# PROMPT 9 - Pre-Submit Rejection Audit (COMPREHENSIVE)

This is your final gate. Check EVERY item below against your complete evaluation.

## A. GROUNDING (addresses Fabrication - 27 rejections)
- [ ] Every strength references specific files/functions/commands FROM the actual response
- [ ] Every weakness points to specific observable failures IN the actual response
- [ ] No claims about things not visible in responses
- [ ] If a response was exploratory only -> evaluated as incomplete, not as implementation
- [ ] No "all tests pass" claims unless test output is quoted
- [ ] No "implemented X" claims unless X's code is visible

## B. CONTRADICTIONS (addresses 67 rejections)
- [ ] No strength contradicts a weakness for same response
- [ ] Framing consistent (not neutral in one place, harsh in another for same topic)
- [ ] No copy-paste errors between A and B fields
- [ ] Same characteristic not praised AND criticized without explicit trade-off framing

## C. RATING ALIGNMENT (addresses #1 reason - 166 rejections)
- [ ] Similar feedback -> ratings in 4-5 range
- [ ] Extreme ratings (1-2, 7-8) have extreme evidence (one fails, one succeeds)
- [ ] Each dimension discussed in feedback before rating it
- [ ] Rationale logically leads to the ratings
- [ ] Ratings are NOT identical across all 9 dimensions
- [ ] More weaknesses for A -> A gets higher numbers (5-8)
- [ ] More weaknesses for B -> B gets lower numbers (1-4)
- [ ] Honesty loser also loses on Overall (or explains why not)
- [ ] Instruction Following loser also loses on Overall (or explains why not)

## D. HONESTY DIMENSION
- [ ] If one response made false claims -> they lose on Honesty (1-2 or 7-8, not 3-4)
- [ ] False claims also hurt Overall rating
- [ ] False claim severity matches penalty: specific false metrics = severe (1-2), minor exaggeration = moderate (3-4)

## E. DEPTH (addresses Thin Evaluation - 113 rejections)
- [ ] Strengths explain WHY, not just WHAT
- [ ] Weaknesses identify technical risks, not just format issues
- [ ] Each point has specific file/function/line evidence
- [ ] Analysis of architectural trade-offs, not just summaries
- [ ] At least one weakness identified per response

## F. LLM DETECTION (addresses 48 rejections)
- [ ] No banned phrases anywhere in output
- [ ] No "the person who wrote the response" or "the author"
- [ ] No em-dashes
- [ ] No formulaic lists of exactly 3 items
- [ ] Sentence structure varies (not every sentence starts the same way)
- [ ] Using contractions throughout
- [ ] No self-validating language ("checking if claims are grounded...")
- [ ] No generic phrases that could apply to any task
- [ ] Output reads like a developer's review, not an AI audit report
- [ ] No "In summary", "Overall", "Moreover", "Furthermore", "It is clear that"
- [ ] Straight quotes only, no curly/smart quotes

## G. CATEGORIZATION
- [ ] Every weakness uses correct predefined category code
- [ ] No technical flaws dumped into "Other"
- [ ] No strengths written in weakness sections
- [ ] At least one weakness checkbox per response

## H. FINAL SANITY
- [ ] Read rationale -> tie or blowout? Rating matches?
- [ ] Would another evaluator reach same conclusions from your evidence?
- [ ] All paragraphs under 5 lines?
- [ ] Evaluation feels unique to THIS task?

